COMPARISON SHOTGUN MAPPING ONTO ASV - METABARCODING

2025-04-03

This scripts present the different steps used for the comparison between shotgun and metabarcoding data based on short-reads mapping into ASVs presented in the paper “Comparison of metabarcoding and shotgun sequencing confirms the relevance of chloroplastic barcodes for lake phytoplankton diversity assessment” (Lemonnier et al., in prep)

SHOTGUN-READS MAPPING ON ASVs

Prepare a fasta file of ASV based on ASV taxonomy table
# load R packages
library(data.table)
library(dplyr)
library(stringr)
library(ggplot2)
library(reshape2)


ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S <- readRDS("Results/Metabarcoding/ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_combined_23S.rds")
ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seqid <- gsub(">","",ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seqid)
write.table(ASV_DADA2_taxonomy, "Results/Metabarcoding/ASV_DADA2_23S_for_fasta.txt" ,quote=FALSE, sep="\t")

# Then awk command to create the fasta file 
# awk '{print ">"$16"\n"$1}' ASV_DADA2_23S_for_fasta.txt > ASV_DADA2_23S_for_mapping.fa
Run 1st mapping with Bowtie2

# Using Bowtie2 v2.5.1

# First, index the ASV fasta
bowtie2-build ASV_DADA2_23S_for_mapping.fa ASV_23S --threads 20

# going through each metagenomic sample, and mapping short reads
# against the ASV fasta files
for sample in `awk '{print $1}' sample.txt`
do
    if [ "$sample" == "sample" ]; then continue; fi
    bowtie2 --threads 20 \
            --very-sensitive \
            --score-min L,0,-0.0 \
            -x ASV_23S \
            -U ../04_SORTMERNA/LSU/${sample}-LSU-rRNA.fq \
            --no-unal \
            -S $sample-in-23S.sam

done

# using Samtools v1.19

for sample in `awk '{print $1}' sample.txt`
do
    if [ "$sample" == "sample" ]; then continue; fi

    # convert the resulting SAM file to a BAM file:
    samtools view -F 4 -bS $sample-in-23S.sam > $sample-in-23S-RAW.bam

    # stats from sam
    #samtools depth $sample-in-23S.sam -o $sample-in-23S.depth

    # sort the BAM file:
    samtools sort $sample-in-23S-RAW.bam -o $sample-in-23S.sorted.bam
    
    # index the BAM file 
    samtools index -b $sample-in-23S.sorted.bam 

    # Get index statistics:
    samtools idxstats $sample-in-23S.sorted.bam > $sample-23S-idxstats.txt

    # Remove temporary files
    rm $sample-in-23S.sam
    rm $sample-in-23S-RAW.bam
    rm $sample-in-23S.sorted.bam

done
Get ASV mapping stats

# Get information on the percentage of ASV length with a read mapping

# Run awk command
for sample in `awk '{print $1}' sample.txt`
do
     #Run awk
     if [ "$sample" == "sample" ]; then continue; fi
     awk '{
  count[$1]++
  min[$1]=(!($1 in min) || $2<min[$1]) ? $2 : min[$1]
  max[$1]=(!($1 in max) || $2>max[$1]) ? $2 : max[$1]
}
END {
  for(i in count) print i,min[i],max[i]
}' $sample-in-23S.depth | column -t >> All_23S_samples_depth_all_LSU.out
done
Filter and keep ASVs with more than 80% of their length with a read mapping
MB23S_stats <- read.table("Results/Metabarcoding/All_23S_samples_depth_all_LSU.out", sep="")

colnames(MB23S_stats) <- c("ASV","min","max")

MB23S_stats$diff <- MB23S_stats$max - MB23S_stats$min

MB23S_stats$phylum <- ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S[match(MB23S_stats$ASV,ASV_DADA2_taxonomy_23S$seqid), "Phylum"]

MB23S_stats$n <- 1

MB23S_occ_cov <- MB23S_stats %>%
  group_by(ASV, phylum) %>%
  summarise(ntime = sum(n))

MB23S_occ_cov80 <- as.data.frame(MB23S_stats %>%
  group_by(ASV, phylum) %>%
  subset(pcov >= 80) %>%
  summarise(ntime = sum(n)))
  
MB23S_occ_cov$n80 <- MB23S_occ_cov80[match(MB23S_occ_cov$ASV, MB23S_occ_cov80$ASV),"ntime"]
MB23S_occ_cov <- subset(MB23S_occ_cov, !n80 == "NA")
for_mapping <- as.data.frame(subset(MB23S_occ_cov, n80 >= 1))

# Save for mapping

  vec<-(genre_table[,s]/totals[s])*100

CO-INERTIA ANALYSIS

# Load packages
library(vegan)
library(ade4)

# Prepare table

# ASV table
MB23S <- ASV_table_23S_perc[,-33]
MB23S <- MB23S[rownames(MB23S) %in% rownames(Mapping_table_23S),]
MB23S$seqid <- rownames(MB23S)

d23SM <- melt(MB23S, id.vars=c("seqid"))
d23SM$variable <- metadata[match(d23SM$variable, rownames(metadata)),"sampleID"]
table_metaB <- dcast(d23SM, seqid ~ variable, value.var=c("value"))
rownames(table_metaB) <- table_metaB$seqid
table_metaB <- table_metaB[,-1]
table_metaB <- as.data.frame(t(table_metaB))

# Add pseudo-count
min_values <- 2/3*(apply(table_metaB , 1, FUN = function(t) min(t[t != 0]))) 
ASV_table_pc <- table_metaB

for (i in 1:32) {
  ASV_table_pc[i,][ASV_table_pc[i,] == 0] <- min_values[i]
  }

# clr transformation
table_metaB23S_clr <- decostand(ASV_table_pc, "clr")


# Mapping table
table_mapp <- as.data.frame(Mapping_table_23S)
table_mapp$tot <- rowSums(table_mapp)
table_mapp <- subset(table_mapp, tot > 0)
table_mapp <- as.data.frame(t(table_mapp[,-c(8,34)]))

# Add pseudo-counts
min_values <- 2/3*(apply(table_mapp, 1, FUN = function(t) min(t[t != 0]))) 
ASV_table_pc <- table_mapp

for (i in 1:32) {
  ASV_table_pc[i,][ASV_table_pc[i,] == 0] <- min_values[i]
  }

# clr transformation
table_mapp23S_clr <- decostand(ASV_table_pc, "clr")
table_mapp23S_clr <- table_mapp23S_clr[rownames(table_mapp23S_clr) %in% metadata$sampleID,]

## PCA of the ASV table
pca_metaB <- dudi.pca(table_metaB23S_clr, 
                     center = TRUE,
                     scale = FALSE,
                     scannf = FALSE,
                     nf = 2) 
## PCA of the mapping table
pca_metaG <- dudi.pca(table_mapp23S_clr, 
                     center = TRUE,
                     scale = FALSE,
                     scannf = FALSE,
                     nf = 2)

# Cumulated relative variation of eigenvalues
cumsum(pca_metaB$eig / sum(pca_metaB$eig)) * 100
cumsum(pca_metaG$eig / sum(pca_metaG$eig)) * 100 


# Performing a co-inertia analysis
coia_ASV_micros <- coinertia(pca_metaG,
                             pca_metaB,
                             scannf = FALSE,
                             nf = 2)


# Monte-Carlo test on the coinertia
mc_test <- randtest(coia_ASV_micros, nrepet = 9999)

# Display results
coia_ASV_micros


# Variance explained by the first two axes in the co-inertia analysis
coia_ASV_micros$eig[c(1:2)]/sum(coia_ASV_micros$eig) * 100
sum(coia_ASV_micros$eig[c(1:2)]/sum(coia_ASV_micros$eig) * 100)

# Get arrows
arrows_start <- coia_ASV_micros$mX
colnames(arrows_start) <- c("Axis1.mX", "Axis2.mX")
arrows_end <- coia_ASV_micros$mY
colnames(arrows_end) <- c("Axis1.mY", "Axis2.mY")
arrows_se <- data.frame(arrows_start, arrows_end)

# First, relative abundance of the same ASVs

genre_table <- as.matrix(ASV_table_23S[rownames(ASV_table_23S) %in% rownames(MB23S_count),])

s_num<-dim(genre_table)[2]
otu.perc<-matrix(rep("NA",times=(dim(genre_table)[1]*s_num)),nrow=dim(genre_table)[1],ncol=s_num)
rownames(otu.perc)<-rownames(genre_table)
colnames(otu.perc)=colnames(genre_table) 
totals<-colSums(genre_table)

for(s in c(1:s_num)){
  vec<-(genre_table[,s]/totals[s])*100
  otu.perc[,s]<-vec
  rm(vec)
}

write.table(otu.perc, "otu.perc_23S.txt")
otu.perc <- read.table("otu.perc_23S.txt", header=T, row.names=1)

ASV_table_23S_good_perc <- as.data.frame(t(otu.perc))
